
                    <div
                      data-cnxml-to-html-ver="[redacted for uniqueness]"
                      data-type="page"
                      id="928aa888-145d-44e7-8249-6c08876d50ff"
                    >
                      <div data-type="abstract" id="[redacted for uniqueness]">
                        By the end of this section, you will be able to:
                        <ul>
                          <li>Identify common particles and energies involved in nuclear reactions</li>
                          <li>Write and balance nuclear equations</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>

                      <p id="fs-idp10810528">
                        Changes of nuclei that result in changes in their atomic numbers, mass numbers, or energy states are
                        <span
                          data-type="term"
                          group-by="n"
                          id="[redacted for uniqueness]"
                        >nuclear reactions</span>. To describe a nuclear reaction, we use an equation that identifies the nuclides involved in the reaction, their mass numbers and atomic numbers, and the other particles involved in the reaction.
                      </p>

                      <section data-depth="1" id="fs-idp49661760">
                        <h3
                          data-type="title"
